"""
Semantic feature vectors for card effects.

Each effect is described by a 22-dimensional vector encoding its mechanical
properties. These features are appended to the card observation vector so
the model has prior knowledge of what each effect does, rather than learning
effect semantics purely from reward signals.

Feature schema (22 dimensions):
    0:  self_attack_bonus               (float, /130)
    1:  opponent_attack_penalty         (float, /130)
    2:  self_hp_heal                    (float, /100)
    3:  self_hp_damage                  (float, /100)
    4:  opponent_hp_damage              (float, /100)
    5:  opponent_hp_heal                (float, /100)
    6:  damage_reduction                (float, /130)
    7:  draws_cards                     (float, /5)
    8:  discards_or_moves_own_cards     (float, /5)
    9:  moves_opponent_cards            (binary)
    10: is_conditional                  (binary)
    11: condition_on_own_attribute      (binary)
    12: condition_on_opponent_attribute (binary)
    13: condition_on_chronos            (binary)
    14: condition_on_hp                 (binary)
    15: condition_on_abyss_or_power     (binary)
    16: condition_on_previous_character (binary)
    17: is_interactive                  (binary)
    18: modifies_chronos                (binary)
    19: reverses_day_night              (binary)
    20: modifies_attribute              (binary)
    21: reduces_power_cost              (binary)
"""


